// fabricated. NONE of these rows carry `verified:true`: earning that requires a page this
// worker actually fetched and read this session, and this pass prioritized breadth across
// brands/categories over the fetch-verification grind (which is the natural next wave —
// see tools/gravel-catalog-1-progress.md). A few load-bearing facts (SRAM XPLR cassette/RD
// ranges, Shimano GRX freehub split, Campagnolo Ekar N3W ranges) are corroborated by the
// research already fetched into data/GRAVEL-MODEL.md / ROAD-GRAVEL-SHARED-STANDARDS.md this
// session (SRAM support articles + Bikerumor Ekar teardown), but the individual SKU rows
// below were NOT independently re-fetched by this worker, so they stay unverified too —
// don't inflate the tier past what was actually confirmed.
//
// NO E-BIKES anywhere in this file (CLAUDE.md hard rule 1) — every e-gravel trim (Crux/Creo,
// Grail:ON, Checkpoint+, Topstone Neo, Revolt E+) is excluded; only acoustic trims appear.
// NO POP-UPS (hard rule 2 — n/a to a data file, noted for completeness).
//
// Field shapes follow GRAVEL-MODEL.md §3 (inherits ROAD-MODEL.md §3), decided per that doc's
// DECISIONS-FOR-DOUGLAS recommendations pending his sign-off: `maxTireByWheel` map (§6-1),
// suspension gravel forks included as rigid-or-suspension data with any fork-travel-vs-frame
// rule left dormant (§6-2), gravel `dropper` slot included (§6-3), Ekar modelled in v1 (§6-5).
// Id prefixes are a LOCAL scheme for this file only (not src/schema.js's ID_PREFIX, which is
// MTB-scoped): gfr frame, gfk fork, gfw frontwheel, grw rearwheel, gti tire, gsft shifter
// (brifter, one row = the L+R pair), gfd front derailleur, grd rear derailleur, gca cassette,
// gch chain, gcr crankset, gbb bb, ghs headset, gbr brake, gro rotor, ghb handlebar, gst stem,
// gsp seatpost, gdp dropper, gsa saddle, gpd pedal, gtp bartape.
//
// KNOWN SCHEMA-VOCAB NON-FITS (gravel-9, 2026-07-21) — real products found this pass whose
// specs don't fit the current vocab; logged rather than force-fit (a missing row beats a
// wrong one, same discipline as an unactivated compat rule):
//   - square-taper BB (older/budget touring-adjacent gravel cranksets, e.g. some Surly builds)
//     — GRAVEL_VOCAB.bb has no square-taper token (bsa-road/bb86/bb30a/pf30/24mm-road/dub/
//     dub-wide/ultra-torque/bbright/t47-road/bb386evo/t47-86 only).
//   - slider dropouts (adjustable-chainstay-length dropouts on some steel/adventure frames,
//     e.g. certain Surly/Salsa builds) — no dropout-type field exists on the gravel frame
//     schema at all yet (MTB's `dropoutType` enum was never ported).
//   - 36.1mm seatpost diameter (a handful of older/boutique steel frames) — GRAVEL_VOCAB.
//     seatpost is ['27.2','31.6','30.9','proprietary'] only.
//   - Wilier's straight (non-tapered) steerer on some of its gravel-adjacent forks — GRAVEL_
//     VOCAB.steerer is ['tapered'] only (road/gravel schema never modeled a straight option,
//     unlike src/schema.js's MTB steerer vocab).
//   - Tumbleweed / Curve's non-standard axle spacings on their bikepacking-oriented gravel
//     frames (their own boutique thru-axle/QR variants, not the catalog's 12x100/12x142
//     convention) — no matching rearAxle/frontAxle token.
// None of these are activated here; a future pass should widen the vocab + add the real rows
// once there's appetite for the schema change, per the same land-dormant-then-activate template
// rule 18/14c already use in src/compat.js.

